description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an organised, calm, efficient and lovely person to come and work with us on Colmers ward as a part time ward clerk.  The post is for 11. 5 hours per week, working Friday 7.5 hours and 4 hours to be agreed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working opposite the other ward clerk, and there will be opportunities of additional hours to cover leave and absence on a &#39;bank&#39; agreement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be to support the team in all aspects of Administration for our busy Elderly care ward. You will have direct contact with patients and families as well as lots of other visiting professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will often be the first and main point of contact to all people coming onto the ward&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are lots of opportunities for personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires a Standard Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:  Rachel Foxley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:  Senior Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:  r.foxley@nhs.net &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:  01308 426239&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Terry Stoodley - Hospital Secretary 01308 426240&lt;/p&gt;
